-- Toyota cuts 08/09 auto sales forecast by 8.5 percent
-- 
-- Mon Dec 22, 2008 1:56am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/12/22/us-toyota-sales-sb-idUSTRE4BL0KF20081222

 

 NAGOYA  (Reuters) - Toyota Motor Corp, the world's largest car maker, on Monday cut its global auto sales forecast by 8.5 percent for the year ending March 2009 amid a worldwide economic downturn. 

 Toyota now expects to sell 7.54 million vehicles during the current business year, down from its previous forecast of 8.24 million. (Reporting by  Chang-Ran Kim )